fields.title: In Person and/or Medication Delivery Pre-Visit Information

Your Specialty medical provider will work with you to determine the best treatment plan.

Not every visit will a require a prescription or an in-person visit. 

But if you end up needing one or both, answering the following questions will speed up the process.
What is your preferred pharmacy name and address?

properties.description: You can also share days of the week that work better if the visit isn't needed today or tomorrow. Ultimately, your provider will assist with the medical recommendations and necessity.  Keep in mind that many factors affect the visit time including location but in general our first visit timeframes start around 9am and our last in-person visit timeframes of the day start between 3 and 4pm

fields.title: Ideally, where would this in-person visit take place?
Please share where:
Please share parking instructions, tips, requests etc (which door, how to let you know we're there, pets, etc.):
Now, we'd like to share what the next steps will be so you know what to expect.

Next you will be prompted to select the type of visit you would like. If you would prefer for the follow-up to be done via chat in our app select "chat visit" for your visit type. If you would prefer a video visit, select "video visit".

If you select "chat visit" for an acute issue, choose a time that you would be most available to respond to your provider within the app. We will respond within a few minutes of your ideal time but we might reach out to you earlier if needed.  We will respond within four hours for non-acute issues, refill requests and chronic issue updates.   

If you select "video visit" your visit will occur at the time you select.
In some cases depending on what your medical provider believes is the appropriate course of action a different visit type may be suggested. We will message you in the app if this is the case.
